turn.0: Hi, I'm your automated assistant. I can answer your questions about Complications of traumatic brain injury.
turn.1: What are some of the complications of traumatic brain injury?
turn.2: The body can repair small blood vessels, but damage to larger ones can result in serious complications.
turn.3: What are some examples of what could happen?
turn.4: Damage to one of the major arteries leading to the brain can cause a stroke, either through bleeding from the artery or through the formation of a blood clot at the site of injury, blocking blood flow to the brain.
turn.6: Blood clots also can develop in other parts of the head.
turn.8: Other types of vascular complications include vasospasm, in which blood vessels constrict and restrict blood flow, and the formation of aneurysms, in which the side of a blood vessel weakens and balloons out.
turn.10: Fluid and hormonal imbalances can also complicate treatment.
turn.12: Hormonal problems can result from dysfunction of the pituitary, the thyroid, and other glands throughout the body.
